-- Taiwan's Mercuries becomes top stakeholder in King's Town Bank -report
-- By Faith Hung
-- Mon Jun 09, 2014 08:32PM EDT
-- None



TAIPEI, June 10 (Reuters) - Mercuries Life Insurance <2867.TW> bought a stake in King's Town Bank <2809.TW> for T$3.2 billion ($106 million), a newspaper said on Tuesday.

The move would make the insurer the top stake holder of the small bank, raising its stake to 9.62 percent, the Commercial Times reported.  The deal was done via bulk trading after market hours on Monday at an average of T$28.38 per share, it said.  King's Town Bank closed at T$28.7.